    {
      "title": "Passive Coast Flight (No Thrust)",
      "description": "This scene is a no-thrust coast model: choose initial speed and direction at launch height, then observe ballistic/gravity-dominated outcomes.",
      "markdown": "# Launch and Insertion Simulator\n\nThis scene ties together **vehicle mass properties** and **orbital targets**.\n\n## Important Modeling Note\n\nThis simplified simulator starts at a **launch-height point** at altitude $h$ (post-ascent), not from ground liftoff. So $h$ is the simulation start height, while $h_{target}$ is the desired orbit height.\n\n## Mass and Propulsion Bookkeeping\n\n- Dry mass: $m_d$\n- Fuel mass: $m_f$\n- Initial mass: $m_0=m_d+m_f$\n\nMaximum ideal one-stage delta-v estimate:\n\n$$\\Delta v_{max}=I_{sp}g_0\\ln\\left(\\frac{m_0}{m_d}\\right)$$\n\n(with $g_0=9.81\\,\\text{m/s}^2$).\n\n## Gravity Inputs\n\nWe compute gravity live from:\n- $G_s=G\\times10^{11}$\n- $M_x=M/10^{24}$\n- $\\mu=G_sM_x\\times10^4$ (km$^3$/s$^2$)\n\n## Target Speeds for Orbit\n\nAt launch-height radius $r=R_p+h$:\n\n$$v_{\\text{circ}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\mu}{r}}, \\quad v_{\\text{esc}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{2\\mu}{r}}$$\n\nIf your speed is below circular, the trajectory is usually suborbital unless direction and staging are corrected.\n\n## Pedagogical Model Used Here\n\nFor interactive clarity, this simulator uses a blended 2D model:\n- ballistic-like arc when speed is below orbital target,\n- near-circular motion around $v_{\\text{circ}}$,\n- outward escape branch near/above $v_{\\text{esc}}$.\n\nThis keeps the controls intuitive while preserving the key speed-height logic used in real orbital mechanics.",
      "prompt": "Teach this as a mission design loop: (1) compute speed targets from height, (2) check delta-v budget from mass and Isp, (3) tune launch direction for insertion quality.",
